<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-12-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1071" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1071">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 431.11 Or 4/172</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-12-20"><hi rend="italic">December 20,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 640.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith a
                            check, drawn on Messrs. G. Amsinck &amp; Co., New York, by the Bank of
                            Venezuela, for sixty-four thousand four hundred and twelve dollars
                            fifty-nine cents ($64,412.59) in payment of the award of The Hague
                            Tribunal in the <hi rend="italic">Orinoco</hi> steamship case.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sheldon
                            Whitehouse.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>